{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17503085","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17503085"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T10:54:41+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T10:54:41+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1931"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"1931","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/1931"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.37,0.03,0.05,0.46,0.1]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1931"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"54330"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"1931","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/1931"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1931"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"39837"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"19"},{"type":"tags","id":"30"},{"type":"tags","id":"36"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"78"},{"type":"tags","id":"934"},{"type":"tags","id":"961"},{"type":"tags","id":"2967"},{"type":"tags","id":"3465"},{"type":"tags","id":"4964"},{"type":"tags","id":"4969"},{"type":"tags","id":"6442"},{"type":"tags","id":"9598"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11644"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"1716"},{"type":"contributions","id":"16542"},{"type":"contributions","id":"35619"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44523"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"54330","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/54330"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EAn 85-year-old woman attends her General Practitioner with a ten-day history of dysuria and frequency. The urine is cloudy and foul-smelling. She has a medical history of a number of urinary tract infections over the previous six months. On examination she looks well with vital signs within normal limits. Abdominal examination is unremarkable apart from some suprapubic tenderness. An abdominal X-ray is performed (Image).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Emphysematous cystitis","Caecal volvulus","Pericolic abscess","Colovesical fistula","Pelvic abscess"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe X-ray shows a large (15 cm) smooth-surfaced structure in the pelvis with an air-fluid interface. This is almost certainly the bladder, filled to capacity with urine and gas. The clinical picture of recurrent urinary tract infections and gas within the bladder would fit well for a \u003Cstrong\u003Efistulous communication between colon and bladder\u003C/strong\u003E. These are often the result of diverticular disease.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe pelvic mass might have some resemblance to an abscess cavity (e.g. \u003Cstrong\u003Epelvic abscess \u003C/strong\u003Eor\u003Cstrong\u003E pericolic abscess\u003C/strong\u003E), with air and a fluid level - but the density below the fluid level is perhaps rather too homogeneous for an abscess. In addition, the patient is in relatively good health and an abscess cavity of this - from whatever origin - would usually be associated with some systemic signs of sepsis.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEmphysematous cystitis\u003C/strong\u003E is rare and the patients are usually ill. In addition, gas would be visible within the bladder wall.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe air and fluid-filled structure is within the pelvic and thus unlikely to be a \u003Cstrong\u003Ecaecal volvulus\u003C/strong\u003E, which tends to show most prominently in the left upper quadrant of the abdomen.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Diverticular disease can result in fistulous communication between colon and bladder, which can result in recurrent urinary tract infections."],"references":["Falidas E, Anyfantakis G, Boutzouvis S, Kyriakopoulos M, Mathioulakis S, Vlachos K et al. Recurrent Urinary Tract Infections due to Asymptomatic Colonic Diverticulitis. Case Reports Med 2012;934168. Available at: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3295588/#:~:text=Colovesical%20fistula%20is%20common%20complication,the%20cause%20of%20colovesical%20fistula."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"39837"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1931"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"11266"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"11266","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/11266"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/4db96a01-8967-4b6d-a694-e95caefb27f2.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/4db96a01-8967-4b6d-a694-e95caefb27f2.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":562,"height":440}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"39837","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/39837"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-10-04T09:19:18+09:30","updatedAt":"2024-10-04T09:20:31+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1931"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"54330"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"19","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/19"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udd2a","name":"General Surgery","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:47:20+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"2"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"30","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/30"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udff4\